      "date": "2023-09-11 19:23:52.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nI'm wondering if we need to touch the modules.order file in Lustre source code directory instead of the unpacked directory in lbuild, because customers are likely not using lbuild.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "145add6f06f0cfd59cd545de51a5662a8c53b4c3",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2023-09-13 08:00:20.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nThis is only going to fix the lbuild usage, not regular build failures using \"rpmbuild\" or whatever Debian/Ubuntu is using, so I think it is only of marginal benefit.\n\nWe don't want to save the actual modules.order file into the sources, but possibly it could be created via \"autogen.sh\" or similar pre-build script that is common across all builds?",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
